The paper deals with lossy source coding problems, which are typically studied in the information theory community. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of test channels, which are commonly used in machine learning and multimedia applications, suggesting cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing) as likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of asymptotics and large deviations, which are common in probability theory and statistics, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories.
